news.title: The Phoenix Mills' net profit grows 36.92% in Q2 FY24
news.para: The Phoenix Mills' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 906.64 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 32.65 per cent from Rs 683.49 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: USA: D.R. Horton sees weaker Q1 as high mortgage rates cool demand
news.para: D.R. Horton, the largest U.S. homebuilder by volume, expects current quarter home sales in the range of 18,500 to 19,000 units, compared with 22,928 in the previous quarter ended September.

news.title: Brigade Enterprises posts net profit of Rs 112.50 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Brigade Enterprises' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,407.92 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 54.35 per cent from Rs 912.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UK's Persimmon says 2024 'highly uncertain' despite home sales pickup
news.para: Improved sales since start of October have left Persimmon upbeat compared with peers Barratt and Vistry, which last month flagged challenges in the British housing market.

news.title: Nexus Select Trust's net profit declines 27.18% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Nexus Select Trust declared distributions of Rs 452.07 crore / Rs 2.98 per unit for the quarter ended September 30, 2023. It achieved net operating income (NOI) of Rs 390.9 crore, a 17% year-on-year growth.

news.title: Canada plans to convert public buildings into new 2,800 homes amid shortage
news.para: The construction would include affordable housing and, combined with previously announced projects for the next five years, Ottawa is now on track to double the number of affordable homes built in the past 30 years, Public Services Minister Jean-Yves Duclos told a news conference.

news.title: WeWork seeks permission to begin canceling leases in bankruptcy
news.para: The Softbank-backed office space-sharing company filed for bankruptcy protection in Newark, New Jersey, bankruptcy court on Monday, seeking to address more than $4 billion in debt and unsustainable rent costs.

news.title: Raymond's net profit dips marginally in Q2 FY24
news.para: Raymond's real estate business recorded a total booking value of over Rs 650 crore and sales performance of Rs 243 crore in Q2 FY24. The segment witnessed revenue of Rs 242.59 crore and profit before tax of Rs 44.41 crore during the said quarter.

news.title: Somany Ceramics posts net profit of Rs 29.53 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Somany Ceramics' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 659 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 6.18 per cent from Rs 620.67 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Birla Corporation posts net profit of Rs 29.53 crore in Q2 FY24
news.para: Birla Corporation's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,313.23 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 13.31 per cent from Rs 2,041.58 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Century Plyboards' net profit grows by 2.78% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Century Plyboards (India)'s net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,011.41 crore in Q2 FY24, a growth of 8.87 per cent from Rs 928.97 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kamdhenu's net profit up 24% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Kamdhenu's net total income stood at Rs 186.59 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 2.61 per cent from Rs 191.60 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Why WeWork failed, and what is next
news.para: WeWork was once the most valuable U.S. startup, worth $47 billion. It courted investments from blue-chip investors, including SoftBank and venture capital firm Benchmark, as well as major Wall Street Banks including JPMorgan Chase.

news.title: DLF to acquire certain stakes is companies owning 63 acres land in Gurugram for Rs 40 crore
news.para: The board of directors of DLF have inter-alia approved acquisition of 5.22% shareholding in Invecon and 4.48% and 3.24% shareholding in its affiliates namely, Vikram Electric Equipment and Uni International, respectively from existing individual shareholders.

news.title: Pune civic body looks to settle dust as construction booms
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation will also introduce new directives, similar to those implemented by the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation, to further regulate construction practices. The teams will monitor dust pollution year-round and ensure compliance with existing norms.

news.title: Peninsula Land's net profit dips 56.09% in Q2 FY24
news.para: Peninsula Land's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 130.22 crore in Q2 FY24, a dip of 58.43 per cent from Rs 313.23 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: LivSYT raises $2.5 million in funding from Silicon Valley Quad, Inventus Cap
news.para: The fresh capital infusion, which pushes the overall sum raised to $4.5 million, will help LivSYT expand into the US market and explore new artificial intelligence and machine learning use cases.

news.title: Vikram Puri acquires hotel in Goa for Rs 60 crore from Sun Estates
news.para: Vikram Puri, the MD of Archer Hospitality, the proprietor of The Astor Kolkata, is set to expand the Astor brand, after more than two decades of overseeing a single hotel property.

news.title: Delhi development body to offer 36,000 flats around Diwali
news.para: "In Dwarka, a total of 3,100 flats will be offered. Apart from 14 penthouses in Sector 19B and 170 super HIG flats, there will be 946 HIG, 316 MIG and 1,654 LIG flats. All will be located mostly in sectors 19B and 14," said an official.

news.title: MahaRERA initiates action against 370 projects in state
news.para: Officials on Tuesday told TOI that these projects were earlier issued show-cause notices and later given a hearing by the MahaRERA after which a penalty of Rs 10,000 to Rs 50,000 was levied on developers.
